# glowstone_cave.tas — Phase-3 block-light regression on a dug flatland cave.
#
# Purpose: dig a small pit into flat terrain, place a glowstone at the bottom
# of the pit, and verify that the per-chunk block-light BFS propagates through
# the surrounding air and brightens the pit interior. Compared against the
# same TAS run with `--place-block=stone` (no emitter placed), the glowstone
# run should show a bright yellow-gold core on the pit floor and a softer
# falloff on the wall faces above it.
#
# Companion runner: `tests/glowstone_cave.sh` — reads both PPMs, computes
# mean brightness inside a bbox centred on the pit (immediate neighbours of
# the glowstone) and in a distant bbox (roughly 4 cells above the pit rim),
# and asserts:
#     near_mean_with_glowstone  >  threshold_bright
#     far_mean_with_glowstone   <  near_mean_with_glowstone
#     near_mean_stone_baseline  <  near_mean_with_glowstone
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#
#   # Baseline: same TAS with stone placed (no emission) — the pit stays dark.
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --world=flatland --aa=none --place-block=stone \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/glowstone_cave.tas \
#     --dump-frame=/tmp/glowstone_cave_stone.ppm
#
#   # Glowstone: same TAS with glowstone placed — pit interior lights up.
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --world=flatland --aa=none --place-block=glowstone \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/glowstone_cave.tas \
#     --dump-frame=/tmp/glowstone_cave_glow.ppm
#
#   # Automated runner with brightness asserts:
#   ./examples/voxel/tests/glowstone_cave.sh
#
# Tick numbering is relative to the first post-loading tick.

# --- Capture mouse ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Look almost straight down so each subsequent dig chews into the
#     same (x,z) column. Matches dig_relight.tas so the dig raycast behaves. ---
3 mouse_move 0 400

# --- Dig three blocks deep: a 1×3×1 vertical shaft. The third dig lands at
#     roughly y = surface - 2, giving us headroom above the glowstone for the
#     block-light BFS to climb back out of the hole. ---
5  mouse_down left
6  mouse_up left
9  mouse_down left
10 mouse_up left
13 mouse_down left
14 mouse_up left

# --- Right-click to place `state.place_block` on the face of the dug hole's
#     floor. The raycast aims at the exposed floor block from directly above,
#     and the place position lands on top of that block — i.e. inside the pit,
#     one cell above the floor. For --place-block=glowstone that emits light
#     into all 6 neighbouring air cells of the pit interior. ---
17 mouse_down right
18 mouse_up right

# --- Tilt the camera up so the hole rim and the glowstone's upward faces are
#     both in frame. This exposes both the bright-near sample region (the
#     pit interior) and the far sample region (flat ground around the rim).---
22 mouse_move 0 -150

# --- Slight horizontal pan so the diagonal interior wall shows the block-light
#     gradient rather than a straight-on head-on shot of a single face. ---
24 mouse_move 4 0
25 mouse_move 4 0
26 mouse_move 4 0
27 mouse_move 4 0

# --- Hold steady so --dump-frame lands on a deterministic final view. ---
32 mouse_move 0 0
